## Preamble

{{ company_name }} ("the Organization") handles sensitive and confidential information on behalf of its clients, partners, and internal operations. The Organization maintains strict confidentiality agreements with its clientele, requiring that all information and materials provided by clients be kept in confidence, in any and all forms, and not disclosed to third parties without the client's express written permission.

As a contractor engaged by the Organization, your access to and work with the Organization is contingent upon your compliance with these confidentiality obligations, which mirror the commitments the Organization has made to its clients.

## 1. Confidential Information

As a contractor, you may have access to what this Agreement designates as "Confidential Material." This Agreement is intended to clarify your obligations regarding such material.

Confidential Material includes, but is not limited to:

- Client, customer, and partner information (including contracts, communications, account data, and business relationship details).
- Financial transactions (including payment records, billing information, and account balances).
- Lists of individuals containing Personally Identifiable Information (PII) or other protected data categories.
- Third-party proprietary information (including software, vendor data, specifications, and methodologies).
- Internal organizational information (including business strategies, financial data, security configurations, trade secrets, source code, and infrastructure details).

All client identities, databases, data sets, software enhancements, programs, updates, electronic media, memoranda, and related materials (collectively "Client Data") are the exclusive property of the Organization and are considered privileged and confidential.

Unauthorized use, access, or disclosure of Client Data - whether generated by the Organization or obtained during the course of your contract work - is strictly prohibited.

## 2. Contractor Obligations

Confidential Material is valuable and sensitive. It is protected by law and by organizational policy. These protections are designed to ensure that Confidential Material is used only as necessary to accomplish the Organization's legitimate business purposes. As a contractor, you are required to adhere to all applicable laws and organizational policies governing Confidential Material. Your principal responsibilities are outlined below.

Violation of any of these obligations may result in termination of your contract and legal action.

### 2.1 Authorized Use Only

You will use Confidential Material solely to perform your legitimate duties as defined in your contract or statement of work. Specifically:

- You will access only the Confidential Material necessary for your contracted work.
- You will not take possession of, divulge, copy, release, sell, loan, review, alter, or destroy any Confidential Material unless explicitly authorized within the scope of your contract.
- You will not misuse Confidential Material or handle it carelessly.
- You will not use Confidential Material for personal benefit or for the benefit of any party other than the Organization.

### 2.2 Safeguarding Access Credentials

You will protect your access credentials (usernames, passwords, access codes, tokens, keys, or any other authorization mechanisms) that permit access to Confidential Material or organizational systems. Unauthorized sharing or disclosure of these access credentials is prohibited.

### 2.3 Responsibility for Actions

You accept responsibility for all actions taken during the course of your contract work. You will promptly report any activities by any individual or entity that you suspect may compromise the confidentiality of information to your Organization supervisor or designated security contact. Reports made in good faith will be handled confidentially to the extent permitted by law.

### 2.4 Continuing Confidentiality

You understand that your obligation to protect Confidential Material continues beyond the termination or expiration of your contract. The Organization may periodically review, revise, or renew your access rights, and you must maintain confidentiality throughout and after the contract period.

### 2.5 No Ownership Rights

You acknowledge that you have no ownership, proprietary rights, or intellectual property interest in any Confidential Material covered under this Agreement, unless otherwise specified in your master services agreement or contract. The Organization reserves the right to revoke your access to Confidential Material at any time, with or without cause.

### 2.6 Accountability for Misuse

You will be held accountable for any misuse, unauthorized possession, or wrongful disclosure of Confidential Material. Failure to safeguard access credentials or other authorizations may result in immediate termination of your contract, forfeiture of compensation, and legal liability, including civil and criminal prosecution.

### 2.7 Return of Materials

Upon termination or expiration of your contract, or upon request by the Organization, you must promptly return or securely destroy all Confidential Material in your possession, custody, or control. This includes all copies, extracts, summaries, and derivative works. You must certify in writing that all such materials have been returned or destroyed.

## 3. Governing Terms

This Agreement supplements and is incorporated by reference into your master services agreement, statement of work, or contract with the Organization. In the event of any conflict between this Agreement and the terms of your contract, the more restrictive confidentiality provisions shall apply.

## 4. Acknowledgment

By signing below, I acknowledge that:

- I have read and understand this Contractor Access and Confidentiality Agreement.
- I agree to comply with all obligations set forth in this Agreement.
- I understand that any breach of this Agreement may result in immediate termination of my contract, forfeiture of compensation, and legal prosecution.
- I understand that my confidentiality obligations under this Agreement survive termination or expiration of my contract.

